<HEADLINE>
FT  21 DEC 94 / Brazilian police seized
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   RIO DE JANEIRO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Three police officers have been taken hostage by farmers protesting at the
creation of a tribal reservation near their land in northern Brazil, Globo
television reported yesterday.
An estimated 10,000 farmers poured into the small town of Montesalves, in
Maranhao state, and are demanding the land earmarked for the indigenous
people. As well as holding the officers, the protestors set fire to a bridge
on a road to the site.
</TEXT>
