FT  21 DEC 94 / Microsoft's share price falls sharply
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Microsoft's share price fell sharply yesterday when the software company
announced another delay in the launch of 'Windows 95', its new version of
the Windows personal computer program.
Shipping of the product may be delayed until August from the expected date
of May or June. It has already been delayed by more than a year. The shares
fell by more than 4 per cent to Dollars 59 7/8 at the close.
