FT  20 DEC 94 / International Company News: Coflexip merges with Stena unit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LASCELLES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Coflexip, the French oilfield services company, yesterday completed a
Dollars 230m merger with Stena Offshore, the offshore contracting arm of
Stena of Sweden, writes David Lascelles. The two companies claimed the deal
would create Europe's largest offshore contracting company, and the world's
seventh largest by market capitalisation.
The merger was financed by issues of shares and convertible Coflexip stock
which, when fully exercised, will give Stena 32 per cent of Coflexip.
Coflexip is based in Paris and had sales of Dollars 379m and profits of
Dollars 33m in 1993. Stena Offshore specialises in sub-sea contracting in
the North Sea. Revenues in 1993 were Dollars 321m and operating profit
Dollars 34m. The combined company will be known as Coflexip/Stena Offshore.
