<HEADLINE>
FT  20 DEC 94 / UK Company News: IMI sells first phase of Holford estate
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL CHEESERIGHT, Midlands Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
IMI, the engineering group, is selling the completed first phase of its
Holford industrial and warehousing estate in Birmingham to Rodamco, the
Dutch group, for Pounds 25m.
The Holford estate is on land owned by IMI near Spaghetti Junction on the M6
motorway. It has been producing rental income of Pounds 2.5m a year and was
valued in the last accounts at Pounds 23m.
IMI has extensive holdings of land which are no longer required for group
operations. 'The Holford estate has never been a core part of IMI,' said Mr
Alan Emson, finance director. 'The market place for this type of development
has improved.'
There has been a steady demand for distribution properties on sites near
motorway junctions in the Midlands and numerous projects have emerged to
compete with established developments like Holford.
The phase being sold to Rodamco cost Pounds 16.5m to develop. Phase two of
the estate thus far involves just one building  - an office block for
Birmingham Cable.
