FT  20 DEC 94 / Christie's overtakes rival Sotheby's
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Christie's, the fine art auction house, has edged ahead of rival Sotheby's
for the first time in nearly 40 years. In the autumn season Christie's
recorded a 10 per cent rise in turnover from Pounds 357m to Pounds 393m
(Dollars 625m). Sotheby's sales fell from Pounds 428m a year ago to Pounds
370m.
Over the year as a whole Sotheby's is slightly ahead, with a turnover of
Pounds 862m compared with Pounds 818m at Christie's.
