FT  19 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Royal Bank lifts stake in motor insurance
venture
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RALPH ATKINS, Insurance Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Royal Bank of Scotland increased by Pounds 5m its investment in a new
motor insurance company set up with Mr Peter Wood of Direct Line after
discussions with the Department of Trade and Industry, the bank's annual
report revealed on Friday.
The bank announced last year that it intended to invest Pounds 24m in
Privilege, which is aimed at 'non-standard' risk drivers, but it increased
its stake to Pounds 29m in May after talks with the DTI, which is
responsible for regulating the insurance industry.
Privilege began trading in the autumn.
Royal Bank of Scotland's decision increased the preference shares it owns in
Privilege to 27.5m from 22.5m. The bank also owns 1.5m ordinary shares and
Mr Wood owns a further 1m.
