<HEADLINE>
FT  19 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Oceonics in the red as finance director
leaves
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Oceonics Group, the lossmaking marine survey company, announced the
departure of its finance director and cuts in executive salaries after
sliding into the red with losses of Pounds 1.69m in the half year to
September 30.
It said Mr Mike Hutchison would be leaving the group at the end of the
current financial year, in which it has cut 131 jobs - 20 per cent of the
workforce - amid weak demand and over-capacity in the offshore oil industry.
The company said Mr David Arnold, the newly appointed group commercial
director, would take over as finance director from Mr Hutchison. The costs
associated with Mr Arnold's appointment were being matched with voluntary
cuts in director compensation.
The loss, against pre-tax profits of Pounds 222,000 last time, was on
turnover down from Pounds 13.2m to Pounds 8.19m. Losses per share were 1.2p
(0.2p).
</TEXT>
